      </div>
      <div class="msgContentFrame">I just wanted to share my personal experience with this class so far.  <br />So I ll just sum up most of the stuff floating though my head and seperate them under a few points. <br /> <br />1st of all <b>some stuff that bothers me</b>, not becauses I'm gonna be Gladi bashing, but I just want it off my chest <br /> <br />- Gladiator shield and sword SP are under the same 500 SP cap per monster killed. <br />- Gladiator and probably some other melee classes, have their weapons break quite damn fast. <br />- Gladiator take more dmg then a non stop casting Thau, with their rank 20 class passive (Thau passive lowers dmg taken while casting by a damn load, I'm talking about a serious dmg difference, might rather have a Thau tank) <br />- (Personal feeling, is that Gladiator just take more dmg then any class to begin with (archer same lvl gets hit by high lvl mob 700 dmg (In this example archer, with way less defense then me) same mob hit me 1k) <br />- The Provoke skill has besides the nasty long cooldown, some crazy Stamina cost. (I'm ok with the cooldown though) <br /> <br /> <br />Ok so now <b>some of the cool stuff about Gladi</b> <br /> <br />- Lets start with the pretty cool plate armor that we ll be wearing! Too bad, there ain't any for Gladi only yet. <br />- Gladi can keep aggro yumm <br />- If you ranked up your shield rank to 10, you will notice that you can become almost invincible (unless hit by skills) for a duration of a whole block (with Aegis Boon) while recovering your hp per blocked hit, now that's really sexy.  <br /> <br />Add the nice rank 20 passive that adds +block duration, and use a &quot;Scutum&quot; type of shield for 99% block and high defense to increase those rates, and you'r a really insane tank for a moment. (Aegis Boon cooldown is 1 min) <br /> <br />- Did I just said that we should use a Scutum shield? Well ain't those awesome, like carrying a little wall with you, and then at shield rank 14, you can actually use shield bash, to slap things with that little wall, cancel whatever they were casting and silencing them up, niceee! (for only 500tp and 30sec CD) <br /> <br />- Now that we'r talking about shields anyway, Phalanx is one of the best Gladiator skills out there so far. Phalanx lets you hit the enemy after blocking an attack, best part about it, Phalanx costs NO stamina, and only 250TP (which you (almost) get in 1 block) <br /> <br />- Rampart is another little gem, you guys might think, yuck 5min cooldown, but gosh that skill adds some crazy (m)defense boost! (and it lasts for quite a bit too) <br />- Red Lotus &amp; Red LotusII, Yuck mp using skills, BUT! 100% hit rate, just get your Thautamage, to rank 16 or 18 and you ll never run out of mp anyway if you add Stygian Spikes or the rank 20 thau mp sucking skill. (I'd go for the spikes, as a tank you get hit anyway, so spikes ll always work for you) <br /> <br /> <br />I ll throw in <b>some of my personal tips</b> for Gladiators aswell <br /> <br />Always use a &quot;Scutum&quot; type of shield, (unless you'r lvling without shield to avoid blocks for sword SP only) <br />The moment you can equip a shield and you can get your hands on a Bronze Scutum, then go ahead and use it for the damn sexy 99% block and sweet defense. <br /> <br />If you'r using Provoke, as your only aggro skill, (which in my case is enough to keep 100% aggro) make sure to 1st do 1~2 hits before actually using provoke, or the skill will almost have no effect. But if you do use it after a hit or 2, it's as good as 100% aggro, and ll last you untill the next voke. (there's always Phalanx, marauder passive, taunt and other stuff, in case you feel like mobs don't hate you enough)  <br /> <br />Pleaaaaaseeeee, DO NOT use the Machuitl weapons (those wooden bat type of weapons), my gladiator never felt so gimped, when I was using one of those, I literally had a 20 miss streak on a blue monkey with that damn piece of wood. So yeah, daggers and swords all the way. <br /> <br />If you feel in need of SP, higher dmg hits give more SP per hit, just restat to high Str while lvling, the real tanking with uber Vit can come later on, there isn't even that much of content yet that needs REAL tanking. <br />On top of this, using Provoke, and other buffs/debuffs, gives SP, also since last patch you can even use cure on others to get a little SP gain. <br /> <br />Get Second Wind from rank 6 Pugilist, it might cost quite some stamina, but you can use it as a means of surviving, combined with aggroing, and just healing up after combat. <br /> <br />Punishing Barbs of rank 10 Thautamage, is a must have! skill for any class out there. I'm serious, get it! <br /> <br />If you need <b>some directions of what other skills to get</b>, here's a few not hard to get lower lvl skills, that will make your tanking/lvling life easier for sure.  <br />Not all of them are a must have, but I'd certainly look into these, if you'r checking out what skills to get from the other classes. <br />  <br />Conjurer: Shock Spikes(r8), Protect(r16), Shell(r16), (most gladi won't use cure/stoneskin much) <br />Thaumaturge: Punishing Barbs(r10), Stygian Spikes(r16), Absorb stat skills (r18), Siphon MP(r20), Firm Conviction (if you can make yourself cast spells, this skill makes you take A LOT less dmg, while casting) <br />Archer: Raging Strike(r4) <br />Lancer: Ferocity(r4), Feint((r20)250tp 100% hit oooh so niceee), Fleet Foot(r20) <br />Marauder: Bloodbath(r6), Defender(r10), Disorient(r18), Intimidation(r20) <br />Pugilist: Second Wind(r6), Taunt(r10), Prime Conditioning(r20)</div>
